Steven owes Jeremy for cleaning $\dfrac{7}{3}$ rooms at a rate of $\dfrac{11}{2}$ dollars per room. To find out how much Steven owes, we need to multiply the rate by the number of rooms cleaned.

\begin{align*}
\dfrac{11}{2} \times \dfrac{7}{3} &= \dfrac{77}{6} \\
\Rightarrow\qquad\dfrac{77}{6} \times \dfrac{1}{1} &= \dfrac{77}{6} \times \dfrac{1}{1}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad\dfrac{77}{6} \div \dfrac{1}{1} &= \dfrac{77}{6}
\end{align*}

The answer is $\boxed{\frac{77}{6}}$.

